    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that the seven assessed credibility factors provide sufficient evidence to support the hemolysis prediction claim at Model Risk Level 3. Three factors (Numerical solver error, Test samples, Equivalency of input parameters) were not assessed but were judged to be beyond the scope of this submission cycle. The team noted these gaps do not, in their view, materially affect the overall credibility conclusion given the favorable GCI results and independent use-error review. Decision: Accepted.",
